Boil a full #kettle{}.

When boiling, pour the water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high
heat. Add the @basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%mins}.

Drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the
side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly
sliced).

Halve the @green pepper{1}(halved and sliced into thin strips) and discard the core
and seeds.

Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Pop the @diced chicken breast{260%g} into a #bowl{} with the @cornflour{20%g},
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, toss to coat.

Once the oil is hot, stir-fry the chicken until golden and cooked through,
~{8-10%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Sprinkle on the @Thai style spice mix{1}.

> TIP: Add less if you don't like too much heat.

When the chicken is cooked, add the red onions and peppers. Stir-fry until
softened, ~{2-3%mins}.

Lower the heat, then stir in the @hoisin sauce{64%g}, @soy sauce{25%g} and
@water{50%ml} and coat the chicken well.

Bring to a bubble, then remove from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Zest and halve the @lime{1}(zested and halved).

Mix the coriander and a squeeze of lime juice through the stir-fry.

When the rice is cooked, fluff it up with a #fork{}. Mix in the lime zest. Taste
and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Chop the remaining lime into wedges.

Share the rice between your #bowls{} and spoon your spicy chicken on top.

Serve with a lime wedge for squeezing over. Enjoy!

> MOD Step 4: If you've chosen to add king prawns to your meal, add the
@?king prawns{150%g} to the pan when you add the onions and pepper.
> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. The
> prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.